  protein: 32 g
time required: 35 minutes
---

Peel and finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and finely chopped) and @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Remove the stalk and the core from the @red pepper{1}(stalk removed and core removed) and chop it into ½cm squares. Roughly chop the @closed cup mushrooms{1}(roughly chopped). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1}. Remove the @flat leaf parsley{2}(leaves removed from stems and roughly chopped) leaves from their stems and roughly chop.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a medium-sized #frying pan{} over a medium-high heat. Add the garlic and onion. Gently fry for ~{1%minute} or until soft. Add the red pepper and mushrooms. Gently fry for a further ~{2-3%mins} or soft.

> Tip: Add a splash of white wine if you have it to help add another depth to this dish!

Boil some water in a #kettle{}. Place the @vegetable stock pot{1} into a large #measuring jug{}. Add about @boiling water{500%ml}. Stir until it's dissolved.

Add the @risotto rice{1} and @smoked paprika{1/2} and @ground turmeric{1/2} to the pepper and onion mix in the frying pan. Stir to coat and mix the ingredients.

Pour in the stock. Add the kidney beans, half of the parsley, the @tomato puree{1}, @fresh peas{1} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Stir to combine and dissolve the purée. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for about ~{20%mins}.

> Tip: Don't be tempted to stir too much - good paella always has a crusty bottom (it's what's known as the 'socarrat')!

Cover the frying pan with a #lid{} for ~{5%mins} before the end of cooking. After this time, check the liquid has all soaked up and take the paella off the heat. Leave the lid on for a further ~{5%mins}. While you're waiting, slice the @lemon{1/2}(sliced into wedges) into wedges (you'll only really need to use half of it) and chop the @black olives{1}.

Serve by garnishing it with the remaining parsley, big wedges of lemon and the olives scattered over the top.

> Tip: Some food trivia - paella is actually a dish that was named after its cooking pan and not a reference to its ingredients!